Pre-ordered yearbooks can be picked up in front of the Middle School on July 8th from 9 AM -11 AM and July 9th from 12 PM -2 PM. You do not need to exit your vehicle, someone will be available to assist you,
If you did not pre-order a yearbook and would like to purchase one, a limited supply is available. The cost is $20.
Books will also be available in the main office Monday through Thursday, 9 AM - 3 PM.
Questions, please email kamarino@wyasd.org.

post_text:
Second-grade students at Lincolnway had a sweet opportunity to name a new donut flavor for a writing activity coordinated by Ms.Christine McKee. The class was paired with Emingee’s, located at Morningstar Market, Thomasville.
Bulldogs Jaydaci Phillips and Brianna Lindenmuth had the winning flavors Holy Sweet Cannoli and Mint Chocolate Chip. The donuts will be created and sold on May 30th and May 31st at the bakery. Winners will be recognized at the bakery on May 31st at 9:30 a.m. Details are in this week's Blue & White.
Stop by this weekend and grab some donuts - #wyproud!
#wyasd Principal Katy Kveragas Christine Schweitzer McKee

post_text:
HIGH SCHOOL GRADES IN SAPPHIRE:

Currently, the information in the Sapphire portal is not a true reflection of current or final grades. Students have until midnight, May 30th, to turn in work. After that time, work will not be accepted.
Data that will determine final grades is still being added by teachers. Final grades will be posted on the portal by June 9th. As stated previously, final grades will not be lower than third marking period grades. Those grades are accessible on the portal for your reference.
Thank you for your patience.
#WYASD

Principal Hoffman
May 8 at 6:36 PM ·

Good Evening West York Families! Although our Registration/Screening event has been cancelled for next week, you can still register your 5 year old for Kindergarten at Wallace for the 2020-2021 School Year! To register, visit our website at: [https://wyasd-sapphire.k12system.com/CommunityWebPortal/Registration/new_registration.cfm?Action=REG_NEW&REG_TYPE_ID=4](https://wyasd-sapphire.k12system.com/CommunityWebPortal/Registration/new_registration.cfm?Action=REG_NEW&REG_TYPE_ID=4)

**Please share this information with families who have students that will be 5 by September 1st!**

If you have already registered, please check your email for a welcome video and updates specific to our incoming Kindergarten families!

Please feel free to reach out to me at jdhoffman@wyasd.org if you have any questions!

High School students needing work permits -
The High School's main office will be open from 11:30 am to 1 pm Wednesdays AND Fridays beginning Wednesday, April 22, through Monday, May 4. To obtain a work permit, the following is required:
*Proof of date of birth (birth certificate, student passport, student's current drivers license or learner's permit, baptismal certificate)
*Parent's/guardian's drivers license
*Parent/guardian and student both need to be present (both need to sign)
This process takes about 10 minutes. Please be advised that we will have measures in place to ensure proper social distancing guidelines are followed. We thank you in advance for your patience and cooperation. #wyasd
https://bit.ly/34UADH8

post_text:
“Be The Light”
This evening at 8:20 p.m., (20:20 military time) the West York Area School District will honor the Class of 2020 and support the nurses, doctors, first responders, and health care providers on the front line of COVID-19 by lighting up our stadium for 20 minutes.
Our scoreboard will display the score 20-20 in honor of this year’s graduating class, while 4th Down and 19 Yards-to-Go will be displayed as the down and distance signifying COVID-19 is on its final down.
Supporting residents are NOT permitted on the stadium or school grounds during this time and should remain home.
To join in at home, take a selfie or video and post it to social media with the tags #wyproud #BeTheLight

shared_text:
Amanda M Steigleman is with Stacy Kipple and 57 others.
March 25 at 4:48 PM ·

Hello West York Friends! As some of you are aware I work in the District's technology department. Tomorrow we start a new adventure and I am asking for some help.... When you come to pick up a device for your student/s could you place a simple sign in one of your passengers-side windows with your student's last name and then their first name/s? (Again students in grades 4-12 only - right now) I am hoping this will help us get our families through quicker and provide our staff with a little assistance (not everyone's last name is super easy to pronounce or spell) 😉. Everyone has been working really hard for our students and I have never been more proud to be a Bulldog! This was not a suggestion of the District... this is just me asking you all a little favor. Thank you in advance for your help - please spread the word!!!

Four WYAHS students recently took home awards at the annual West York VFW Post 8951 audio-essay contest "What Makes America Great?"

(Pictured, L-R): Chloe Hoover, 11th-grade, tie for 1st Place; Zoha Wasim, 11th-grade, tie for 1st Place, and Alyssa Denney, 2nd Place.
Not pictured, Madge Myers, 11th-grade, 3rd Place.
Chloe Hoover also took 5th Place in the district-level competition! Students were awarded monetary gifts, certificates, and medals.
#wyasd #wyproud

post_text:
The WY Model UN, facilitated by Ms. Melissa Carl, attended the YMCA Hershey Region Model UN Conference from Jan. 3rd-5th. Over 2,000 students were in attendance, with some school delegations numbering over 200. The team as a whole won an Outstanding Delegation Award, and three students won individual awards on their committees: Senior Katherine Hutton won the Outstanding Paper Award representing Japan on the Historical Security Council. Senior Awaiz Zahra won the Premier Delegate Award representing Pakistan on the Asia-Pacific Summit, and Junior Sean Fleming won the Premier Delegate Award representing France on Security Council. WY attends this conference annually and looks forward to going again next year!
#wyproud
